Overview
This module focused on analyzing network packet captures to identify malicious traffic patterns, C2 communication, data exfiltration, 
and other suspicious activity. Wireshark was the primary tool used throughout this module.

Key Concepts Covered

Navigating and filtering packet captures in Wireshark
Identifying common protocols and their expected behavior (HTTP, DNS, SMB, FTP)
Detecting anomalous traffic patterns such as beaconing, port scanning, and unusual data transfers
Extracting files and artifacts from packet captures
Analyzing DNS traffic for signs of tunneling or C2 communication


