Key Takeaways
Network analysis is often about finding what stands out — unusual destination IPs, unexpected protocols, or traffic at odd times. 
DNS is frequently overlooked but is one of the most abused protocols for both C2 communication and data exfiltration due to how rarely it is blocked.
Establishing a baseline of what normal traffic looks like for an environment is essential before anomalies can be reliably identified.
